<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8203891>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Afrotrombicula zairiensis (Taufflieb, 1966), comb. nov., holotype (A, B) and paratype (C–E). A, dorsal aspect of idiosoma; B, ventral aspect of idiosoma; C, dorsal idiosomal seta; D, humeral seta; E, preanal seta. Abbreviations as in Fig. 5. Scale bars: 100 µm (A, B), 20 µm (C–E)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8203891/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8203893>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. Afrotrombicula zairiensis (Taufflieb, 1966), comb. nov., holotype (D–H) and paratype (A–C). A, scutum (eyes not shown, one AL broken, sensilla lost); B, dorsal aspect of gnathosoma; C, ventral aspect of gnathosoma; D, leg I, genu–tarsus; E, leg I, trochanter–telofemur; F, leg II, trochanter–tarsus; G, leg III, trochanter–telofemur; H, leg III, genu–tarsus. Abbreviations as in Fig. 6. Scale bars: 50 µm (A, D–H), 20 µm (B, C)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8203893/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

